{
  "doc_id": "23019",
  "text": "Template selection was done using the HHpred server [CITATION_1] . After template selection, a targettemplate sequence alignment was built with HHpred's builtin alignment function. Additionally, the target-template alignments were compared with the multiple sequence alignments produced with PROMALS3D to verify overall accuracy, and no further editing was performed. The homology models of the chemotaxis proteins, CheB, CheC, CheD, CheR, CheW, CheY of B. amyloliquefaciens FZB42 were calculated using available crystal structures of their homologs, obtained from the Protein Data Bank (PDB). The respective templates used were: 1A2O [CITATION_2] ), 1XKR [CITATION_3] ), 2F9Z [CITATION_4] , 1AF7 [CITATION_5] , 2QDL [CITATION_6] ), 1TMY (Usher et al. 1998) , respectively. For further information on target-template matches, see Table 1 . The target-template alignments were used as inputs for the program MODELLER-9v7 for homology modeling [CITATION_7] . When needed, problematic loops were refined using MODELLER. The models were evaluated based on their discrete optimized protein energy (DOPE Z) scores and MetaMQAPII results [CITATION_8] .",
